  "text": "Chromium Renderer Process Sandbox Audit Summary:\n\n1. LINUX SECCOMP-BPF BASELINE POLICY:\n   Location: sandbox/linux/seccomp-bpf-helpers/baseline_policy.h and baseline_policy.cc\n   Key Class: BaselinePolicy (line 27 in .h file)\n   Description: This class implements the Policy interface with a \"baseline\" seccomp-BPF policy for use within Chromium. It provides the foundation for Linux kernel attack surface reduction by defining system call filtering policies.\n   Key Method: EvaluateSyscall(int system_call_number) const override - evaluates whether a specific syscall should be allowed or blocked\n   Base Class: bpf_dsl::Policy\n   Constructor: BaselinePolicy() and explicit BaselinePolicy(int fs_denied_errno)\n\n2. WINDOWS SANDBOX POLICY BASE:\n   Location: sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy_base.h and sandbox_policy_base.cc\n   Key Class: PolicyBase (line 165 in .h file)\n   Description: This is a final class implementing TargetPolicy that represents the concrete Windows sandbox policy configuration. It manages token levels, job objects, handle restrictions, process mitigations, and AppContainer profiles for Windows processes.\n   Key Methods:\n     - GetConfig() - returns TargetConfig*\n     - InitJob() - creates Job object with specified level\n     - MakeTokens() - creates initial and lockdown tokens\n     - ApplyToTarget() - applies sandbox to target process\n     - EvalPolicy() - evaluates IPC policy rules\n   Constructor: explicit PolicyBase(std::string_view key)\n   Destructor: ~PolicyBase() override\n\n3. RENDERER PROCESS LINUX POLICY:\n   Location: sandbox/policy/linux/bpf_renderer_policy_linux.h and bpf_renderer_policy_linux.cc\n   Key Class: RendererProcessPolicy (line 19 in .h file)\n   Description: This BPF policy is specifically designed for renderer and worker process sandboxing on Linux/ChromeOS/Android. It extends BPFBasePolicy and can be used by both renderer and worker processes.\n   Key Method: EvaluateSyscall(int system_call_number) const override (line 33) - evaluates syscalls specific to renderer processes\n   Constructors:\n     - Linux/ChromeOS: RendererProcessPolicy() (line 22)\n     - Android: explicit RendererProcessPolicy(const BaselinePolicyAndroid::RuntimeOptions& options) (lines 24-25)\n   Base Class: BPFBasePolicy\n\n4. SANDBOX TYPE ENUMERATION:\n   Primary Location: sandbox/policy/mojom/sandbox.mojom (lines 13-176)\n   Supporting Header: sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.h\n   Key Enum: Sandbox (enum class in sandbox::mojom namespace)\n   Description: Defines all sandbox types that can be specified as attributes on Mojo interfaces. This is the authoritative mapping of sandbox type identifiers.\n   Key Enum Values:\n     - kService - computation only services with limited OS access\n     - kServiceWithJit - computation services with dynamic code (v8/wasm)\n     - kUtility - generic utilities with limited system service access\n     - kRenderer - most restrictive, for hosting untrustworthy web content\n     - kGpu - GPU service with driver/OS API access\n     - kNoSandbox - runs with browser rights\n     - kNetwork - network service\n     - kAudio - audio service\n     - kCdm - content decryption module\n     - And many platform-specific variants (kIconReader, kMediaFoundationCdm, kPdfConversion, etc.)\n   \n   Utility Functions in sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.h:\n     - IsUnsandboxedSandboxType(sandbox::mojom::Sandbox)\n     - SetCommandLineFlagsForSandboxType()\n     - SandboxTypeFromCommandLine()\n     - StringFromUtilitySandboxType()\n     - UtilitySandboxTypeFromString()\n\nAudit Findings:\nThe Chromium sandbox architecture follows a layered approach:\n- Linux/Android: Uses seccomp-BPF filtering with BaselinePolicy as the foundation and RendererProcessPolicy for process-specific restrictions\n- Windows: Uses PolicyBase to configure job objects, token levels, and process mitigations\n- The SandboxType enum provides a centralized mapping of all sandbox configurations used throughout the Chromium codebase\nAll files examined are in the core sandbox implementation directories and represent the critical security boundaries for renderer process isolation."
}

